GraphQL Dashboard (Vanilla JS)

A lightweight Single Page Application (SPA) using GraphQL queries, vanilla JavaScript, and a custom router to display user data, graphs, and interactive sections.

<p align="center"> <img src="https://img.shields.io/badge/JavaScript-ES6+-F7DF1E?style=for-the-badge&logo=javascript" /> <img src="https://img.shields.io/badge/GraphQL-API-E10098?style=for-the-badge&logo=graphql" /> <img src="https://img.shields.io/badge/SPA-VanillaJS-00C4CC?style=for-the-badge" /> </p>
ğŸ“ Overview

GraphQL Dashboard is a simple but powerful frontend-only project that consumes GraphQL APIs to show:

User information

XP and levels

Transactions

Graphs

Dashboard pages

It includes:

Custom fetch wrapper

Mini SPA router

Dynamic graph rendering

JWT authentication

Clean UI using plain HTML/CSS

âœ” No frameworks
âœ” No libraries
âœ” 100% Vanilla JavaScript

